{"parse":{"title":"Convergence (sustainability science)","pageid":31360712,"revid":749293513,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Convergence</b> in <a href=\"/wiki/Sustainability_science\" title=\"Sustainability science\">sustainability sciences</a> refers to mechanisms and pathways that lead towards <a href=\"/wiki/Sustainability\" title=\"Sustainability\">sustainability</a> with a specific focus on 'Equity within biological planetary limits'. These pathways and mechanisms explicitly advocate equity and recognise the need for redistribution of the Earth's resources in order for human society to operate enduringly within the Earth's biophysical limits.\n</p><p>This use of the term 'convergence' harkens from the concept of <a href=\"/wiki/Contraction_and_convergence\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Contraction and convergence\">contraction and convergence</a> (C&amp;C), taking its core principles of Equity and Survival and applying them beyond the frame of <a href=\"/wiki/Greenhouse_gas_emissions\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Greenhouse gas emissions\">greenhouse gas emissions</a> to the wider sustainability agenda.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Convergence_(sustainability_science)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Fortnam, Matt. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.convergeproject.org/node/51\">\"Convergence:   How can it be a part of the   pathway to sustainability?\"</a>. The CONVERGE project website<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 April</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Convergence%3A+++How+can+it+be+a+part+of+the+++pathway+to+sustainability%3F&amp;rft.pub=The+CONVERGE+project+website&amp;rft.aulast=Fortnam&amp;rft.aufirst=Matt&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.convergeproject.org%2Fnode%2F51&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AConvergence+%28sustainability+science%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Convergence_(sustainability_science)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.convergeproject.org\">The CONVERGE project website</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1329\nCached time: 20180909001514\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.048 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.065 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 109/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1884/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 100/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1114/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.021/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.34 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   56.270      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   56.270      1 -tot